   PRISON-GUARDS (Sacramento, Calif.) _ In the closing hours of the
1999 legislative session, the administration of California Gov.
Gray Davis quietly tried to give the prison guard union $4 million
in public money for its legal defense fund, a highly unusual favor
to a major political donor. Exposed and excoriated by fellow
Democrats, Davis agreed to remove the provision moments before the
Legislature approved a pay raise and other perks for the
25,000-member California Correctional Peace Officers Association.
By ROBERT SALLADAY.
