 Tuesday, Sept. 14, 1999     
 Editors      The Hearst News Service will file the following for
Wednesday. If you have questions, please call Susie McBee or Tim
Spence at 202-298-6920.    (The ``HNS'' tag appears in all
sluglines.)   
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CONGRESS-VIEQUES (Washington) _ The struggle over a U.S.
military target range on Puerto Rico's Vieques island turns into
political hardball. Sen. James M. Inhofe, chairman of the Senate
Armed Services panel on military readiness, threatens to dismantle
a huge U.S. naval station there unless the Puerto Ricans allow the
U.S. Navy and Marines to resume target practice on Vieques. By
STEWART M. POWELL.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ Right-wing media motormouth Patrick
Buchanan is always spoiling for a good political fight. A
presidential bid on the Reform Party ticket would make him just a
spoiler. But he's generated little support for his current GOP
presidential campaign. How much damage to the major parties would
he really do? By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
</TEXT>
