<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   HIGH-SPEED-TRAIN (Undated) _ Despite Amtrak's promises, many had
suspected the nation's largest passenger rail company, a
debt-ridden, 29-year-old business with a can't-do-anything-right
reputation, wouldn't be ready with high-speed rail by the end of
1999. A firm date won't be announced until early November. By
Thomas Palmer. 1300 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   DYING-MALLS (Hadley, Mass.) -- Across the country, enclosed
