SOME GOOD DEALS FOR THE TRAVELER 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By JERRY MORRIS  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Purchase ``Bed &AMP; Breakfasts and Country Inns'' (11th edition)
and receive a free night at any of more than 1,600 inns in the
guidebook. Inside every copy is a buy-one-night-get-one-night-free
certificate. The free night offer is good through Dec. 31, 2000.
Depending on your choice of inn, the free night is worth from $50
to $650. The book is produced by American Historic Inns and
available by writing to PO Box 669, Dana Point, CA 92629 or calling
800-397-4667. If you mention The Boston Globe, the book is $16.95
(a $5 discount) plus $2.75 shipping (75 cents each for additional
guides).
</P>
<P>
   Everyone (I think) needs underwear. From Sept. 15 through Dec.
31, anyone who purchases five Joe Boxer men's or women's product
will also receive a companion ticket to fly Virgin Atlantic Airways
to London for $99 plus tax. The tickets are good for travel from
the United States between Jan. 1 and June 15, 2000. The companion
ticket is valid with the purchase of an economy-class ticket (21-45
day advance purchase). There is approximately $82 in departure
taxes and fees for the two tickets. The Joe Boxer products will
have tags with details of the offer.
</P>
<P>
   MasterCard has joined with America West Airlines, Virgin
Atlantic, British Midland, and Air New Zealand to offer promotional
fares that provide free or heavily discounted companion fares. The
America West deal is a 50 percent off companion ticket (call
800-2FLY-AWA and ask for tour code P9934); the Virgin offer is a
free companion ticket (call 888-747-7477 ask for code MCOFFER; the
British Midland deal is $99-and-up one-way flights from London to
European destinations (call 888-747-7477 and ask for code MCOFFER);
the Air New Zealand offer is for a free companion Vacation Package
(call 888-781-5170 and ask for MCNZI). Call for information on
flying dates and restrictions. Offers are available through travel
agents.
</P>
