<HEADLINE>
SERIAL KILLER WAS SUBJECT OF 1986 TV MOVIE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: What's the name of the movie about the serial killer
Christopher Wilder? Also, are there any books about him?
</P>
<P>
   _ B.M., Fort Worth, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Wilder was the subject of ``Easy Prey,'' a 1986 made-for-TV
movie starring Gerald McRaney as the serial killer. Shawnee Smith
portrayed Tina Marie Risico, a 16-year-old whom Wilder kidnapped
and forced to participate in another abduction.
</P>
<P>
   Bruce Gibney wrote about Wilder in ``The Beauty Queen Killer,''
a book that was reissued in 1990. You may be able to special order
it from bookstores using ISBN 1-5581-7345-5.
</P>
<P>
   Wilder, a millionaire businessman and race car driver, raped and
killed eight women from February to April 1994 and abducted three
others who escaped. He shot himself in a struggle with New
Hampshire state troopers in a town near the Canadian border.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I write to Stephen King?
</P>
<P>
   _ K.R., Haltom City, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Write to Stephen King, 49 Florida Ave., Bangor, ME 04401, or
visit his official World Wide Web site at www.stephenking.com.
</P>
<P>
   On June 19, King was struck by a van as he was walking near
Lovell, Maine. The 51-year-old writer suffered numerous injuries,
including a broken hip, fractured pelvis and collapsed lung. An
``accident recovery update'' on his Web site indicates King is
doing well.
</P>
<P>
   ``He spends more time out of bed each day, using a walker or
wheelchair,'' King's wife Tabitha writes. ``Stephen has resumed
work on his current writing project, using a laptop and writing for
an hour and a half each day.''
</P>
<P>
   In lieu of flowers and other get-well gifts, the Kings request
that donations be made to a Bangor YMCA summer camp: the Camp
Jordan Capital Campaign, 101 Camp Jordan Way, Ellsworth, ME 04605.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I write to Disney and give my comments about what I
think about their movies?
</P>
<P>
   _ A.W., Burleson, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Send your letter to Chairman Michael Eisner, Walt Disney Co.,
500 S. Buena Vista St., Burbank, CA 91521-1010.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. Contact him at the Fort Worth Star-Telegram, Box
1870, Fort Worth, TX 76101, or e-mail him at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
