<P>
   BURKE _ NEW YORK _ William A. Burke, president of TBS
Superstation and Turner South, has been named president and CEO of
news and information for Time Warner Digital Media, it was
announced today by Richard Bressler, chairman and CEO of Time
Warner Digital Media. Burke will assume his new duties October 4.
In his new position, Burke, 33, will report to Bressler and will
work closely with the management of CNN News Group, Turner
Broadcasting and Time Inc. to develop a business plan for the news
and information vertical hub, building on the strength of CNNis and
Time Inc.is existing interactive news and information businesses.
The editorial functions of the news operations of CNN and Time Inc.
will continue to report to their existing management. (Katz,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 10.
