<P>
   HURRICANE FLOYD
</P>
<P>
   FLOYD-MAIN _ From Florida to North Carolina, nearly 2 million
people were urged to get out of the way of Hurricane Floyd as one
of the most powerful storms of the century threatened to tear up
the Southeast ``like a weed-eater going up the coast.'' Floyd's eye
was expected to pass within 90 miles of southern Florida on
Tuesday, and perhaps within 50 miles of north Florida by Wednesday
morning, before striking land somewhere farther north. Main news
lead. (ABrice, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 30
</P>
<P>
   w/FLOYD-EVACUEES _ Authorities urged nearly 2 million people to
evacuate coastal areas from Florida to North Carolina today as
Hurricane Floyd, one of the most powerful storms to threaten the
United States, roared through the Bahamas. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   FLOYD-JOURNAL _ COCOA BEACH, Fla. _ When getting your home (and
life) prepared for a Category 4 hurricane like Floyd, you
definitely have to sweat the details -- that thin gap underneath
the hurricane-proof garage door, what to do with the pets if you're
evacuated from that carefully chosen inland hotel, garbage cans
left outside, etc. It's those little things that can mean the
difference between returning a relatively dry or water-soaked home,
or even life and death. Developing. (MWilliams, Cox News Service).
15. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   FLOYD-FEMA _ ATLANTA _ Atlanta is the staging area for the
Federal Emergency Management Agency's relief efforts after Floyd is
done. Most of the supplies are currently stored at Fort Gillem.
(Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   FLOYD-FLA _ DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. _ With scary memories of Andrew
7 years ago, most of Florida braced for what could be the century's
biggest hurricane. Even if Floyd slams into Charleston, it was
expected to whip 100 mph winds against Florida's east coast.
(Manuel, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   FLOYD-GA _ BRUNSWICK, Ga. _ After decades of escaping the really
big hurricanes, will the Georgia coast finally take a big hit? The
AJC covers the evacuation of Chatham County (Savannah) Tuesday and
waits to see where Floyd strikes land. (JDavis, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   FLOYD-SC _ CHARLESTON,S.C. _ This historic city appeared the
most likely target for landfall. The AJC is on the scene for
evacuation, preparations 10 years after Category 4 Hugo rumbled
through the Carolinas. (Burritt, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
<P>
   FLOYD-NC _ Folks in Bethel, Washington and Chocowinity and other
communities around the Pamlico Sound face prospects of new storm,
even though they haven't finished cleaning up from the last one.
(Greenville Daily Reflector). WITH POSSIBLE PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   FLOYD-THETURN _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ A look at the dynamics
of how weather systems work to make hurricanes turn north as they
approach Florida (Hurricane Floyd has reportedly begun turning).
(Kleinberg, Palm Beach Post). 30.
</P>
<P>
   FLOYD-DOPPLER _ Several research groups are putting doppler
radar equipment on people 's houses. The research equipment will
help them study hurricanes. (Kleinberg, Palm Beach Post). 15 WITH
PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   FLOYD-PORT _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Port authorities have sent
freighters to sea in advance of Hurricane Floyd. An explainer on
why it's important to get ships out of ports when big storms
approach. (Smith, Palm Beach Post). 10.
</P>
<P>
   FLOYD-ZOOS _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ A report on what zoos have
done with their animals. (Omeilia, Palm Beach Post). 15.
</P>
