<P>
   POLITICS
</P>
<P>
   BRADLEY _ Democrat Bill Bradley snatched a symbolic
environmental endorsement Tuesday from Friends of the Earth,
scoring a minor coup over Vice President Gore. The endorsement is
the latest suggestion that Gore can take no segment of the
Democratic base for granted. The most important environmental
endorsement, however, will come from the Sierra Club, the largest
environmental group and the one with the biggest network of
volunteers. (Foskett, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   GORE-ENVIRONMENT _ WASHINGTON _ Vice President Al Gore, one of
the most active backers of environmental issues in public life, has
been promised a ``surprise'' Tuesday when the key environmental
group. The ``Friends of the Earth'' announces its endorsement in
the presidential campaign. (Shepard, Cox News Service). 18.
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (p) politics categories.
</P>
<P>
   GORE-HISPANICS _ WASHINGTON _ Vice President Al Gore launches
``Ganamos con Gore'' (''Win with Gore''), his presidential
campaign's effort to win the increasingly important Hispanic vote.
Gore is expected to receive endorsements from Latino officials and
community activists from across the country. (Shepard, Cox News
Service). 18.
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (p) politics categories.
</P>
<P>
   SOUTH-FOOTE _ WASHINGTON _ Author and historian Shelby Foote
appears Wednesday at a congressional breakfast hosted by his fellow
sons of Mississippi, Senate Majority Leader Trent Lott and National
Endowment for the Humanities chairman Bill Ferris, to speak on what
makes the South the South and the importance of regionalism in
American culture. (Dart, Cox News Service). 25.
</P>
<P>
   TAX-INTERESTS _ WASHINGTON _ Now that the Republicans' $792
billion tax-cut bill appears to be going nowhere, what are the
options for the corporate lobbyists who have major tax preference
provisions attached to the bill? (Malone, Cox News Service). 20.
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories
</P>
<P>
   Y2K-TRAVEL _ WASHINGTON _ The State Department on Tuesday issues
its list of countries that travelers should avoid because of Y2K
concerns. What it means for the travel industry, airlines, tourists
and business travelers. (Gewax, Cox News Service). 25.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: Y2K-TRAVEL-LIST
</P>
