<P>
   AIRPORT-GROWTH (Los Angeles) _ Van Nuys Airport, the largest
municipal airport in the country, generated $1.23 billion in
economic activity last year, up 30 percent from 1991, and supports
more than 10,000 jobs, up 14 percent over the same period,
according to a report released Tuesday. Keys to the facility's
growth have been the improvement in the Southern California economy
and the rising interest in aviation among corporate executives. By
Dave McNary.
