<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Sept. 15 and thereafter. For questions about stories, please
contact Susan Leh at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   BELMONT-REPORT (Los Angeles) _ An internal LAUSD investigation
of the Belmont Learning Center scandal found massive wrongdoing by
numerous district officials and contractors and called for criminal
investigations, lawsuits and possible dismissal of those
responsible, including Superintendent Ruben Zacarias. By Beth
Barrett and Greg Gittrich. (Will move in the ``n'' California and
``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   BELMONT-CULTURE (Los Angeles) _ The Mullinax report struck at
the heart of what critics have long said is L.A. Unified's biggest
problem: low- and mid-level bureaucrats run the district with very
little leadership or oversight and have created a ``culture of
lying.'' By Beth Barrett. (Will move in the ``n'' California and
``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   BELMONT-SUPERINTENDENT (Los Angeles) _ Superintendent Ruben
Zacarias failed to exercise diligent oversight of the site
acquisition and school development process, a failure that allowed
subordinates to disregard student safety and fiscal prudence,
according to the internal report issued Tuesday. By Greg Gittrich.
(Will move in the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   DISNEY-HALL (Los Angeles) _ Los Angeles County supervisors
agreed to spend $8 million on upkeep and operation of the Disney
Hall, a Frank Gehry-designed facility across from the Music Center
that will be home to the Los Angeles Philharmonic. The hall costs
$209 million and is expected to be finished in time for the L.A.
Philharmonic's fall 2002 season. By Troy Anderson. (Will move in
the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   UCLA-CHARGES (Los Angeles) _ Chicago Bears quarterback Cade
McNown, charged with illegal use of a handicapped-parking placard,
was injured and entitled to the special parking privileges, his
attorney said. Prosecutors said they have videotape of McNown
practicing. McNown and three other former UCLA football players
were not in court for their arraignment, which was postponed. By
Michael Coit. (Will move in the ``n'' California, ``s'' sports and
``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   AIRPORT-GROWTH (Los Angeles) _ Van Nuys Airport, the largest
municipal airport in the country, generated $1.23 billion in
economic activity last year, up 30 percent from 1991, and supports
more than 10,000 jobs, up 14 percent over the same period,
according to a report released Tuesday. Keys to the facility's
growth have been the improvement in the Southern California economy
and the rising interest in aviation among corporate executives. By
Dave McNary. (Will move in the ``f'' financial news file.)
</P>
