<SLUG> BC-BONADUCE-STARFM-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DANNY BONADUCE IN, FRANK AND FROSTY OUT AT STAR-FM 
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients)  
By FRED SHUSTER 
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Danny Partridge has replaced Frosty and Frank in
the morning at Star 98.
</P>
<P>
   Danny Bonaduce, who played the freckled imp on ABC-TV's ``The
Partridge Family'' in the '70s, joins Jamie White for ``The Jamie &AMP;
Danny Show,'' beginning at 5 a.m. today.
</P>
<P>
   White previously co-hosted Star 98's morning show with Frosty
Stillwell and Frank Kramer, who will both remain part of station
owner AMFM Inc.'s talent pool, said Ken Christensen, Star's vice
president and general manager, who added that there were no
immediate plans for the duo. AMFM is the nation's largest radio
broadcasting company, with 446 stations in 101 markets, including
local outlets Mega 100, the Beat, KBIG-FM, KLAC-AM, KOST-FM and
KFI-AM.
</P>
<P>
   Most recently, Bonaduce, 40, hosted mornings at New York's
WTJM-FM and before that worked at stations in Detroit and Chicago.
Bonaduce had success in the Midwest, but his New York program was
overshadowed by shows like Howard Stern's.
</P>
<P>
   White said she grew up watching the red-haired Bonaduce on TV,
adding she was ``delighted over the opportunity to work
side-by-side with him.''
</P>
<P>
   White, Stillwell and Kramer were brought to Star from Denver's
KALC-FM in February 1998. The trio traveled the shock-jock route,
focusing on sex and gossip. Ratings were solid in adult
contemporary Star's target demographic _ women ages 25 to 34 _ and
often in the Top 15 among broader groups of listeners.
</P>
<P>
   Bonaduce hinted the new morning show would follow familiar
lines, referring to White's strong following and ``on-air antics.''
It's expected there will be a focus on celebrity interviews.
</P>
<P>
   Incidentally, ABC-TV is currently shooting ``Come On, Get Happy:
The Partridge Family Story,'' to air in next year. Shawn Pyfrom
will play Bonaduce. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-09-14-99 1905EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> NYT19990914.0216 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-14 19:10 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A1989 &Cx1f; ttj-z
u s BC-BBA-OAKLAND-A's-HNS &LR;      09-14 0761
