   NY-POLLUTION-SUIT (New York) _ After a series of setbacks
against efforts by Northeastern states and federal environmental
officials to limit pollution blowing from coal-fired power plants
in the Midwest, New York state is opening up a new legal front,
announcing its intention Tuesday to file suit against specific
power plants in Ohio and other upwind states to force them to clean
up. By Andrew C. Revkin.
</P>
<P>
   1-column hed.
</P>
<P>
   (We plan to move this story by 8 p.m. ET in `a' news file.)
