<P>
   (NYT12) JERSEY CITY, N.J. -- Sept. 14, 1999 --
GIANT-SCREEN-FILMS, 09-14 -- Giant-screen films like this one in
Jersey City are beginning to add more narrative to their visual
spectacle. Shot with a 70-millimeter camera and chockablock with
spectacular adventure and nature scenes, the giant-screen movie has
become a hugely popular fixture at 300 specially equipped theaters
around the country, but it is experiencing an identity crisis.
(Norman Y. Lono/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT11) UNDATED -- Sept. 14, 1999 -- KOHLRABI, 09-14 -- Kohlrabi
is a tuber related to both cabbage and turnips, all three being
members of the Brassica family. The dual character of the vegetable
is reflected even further in the fact that crunchy, sweet, tangy
kohlrabi is the same vegetable as the woody, stringy, bitter
variety that so often turns people off kohlrabi. The difference
lies in the freshness of the bulb. (Tony Cenicola/New York Times
Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT10) SEBRING, Fla -- Sept. 14, 1999 -- HURRICANE-FLOYD-5,
09-14 -- Residents of assisted living facilities near Florida's
Atlantic coast arrive at The Palms of Sebring, a similar facility
in central Florida, on Tuesday. As well as transporting the
residents, rental trucks were used to bring in wheelchairs, walkers
and other pieces of equipment used by the elderly evacuees.
Authorities urged nearly 2 million people to evacuate coastal areas
stretching from Florida to North Carolina on Tuesday as Hurricane
Floyd, one of the most powerful and biggest storms to ever threaten
the United States, inched closer. (Kathleen Shannon/Sebring News
Sun)
</P>
<P>
