   (NYT11) UNDATED -- Sept. 14, 1999 -- KOHLRABI, 09-14 -- Kohlrabi
is a tuber related to both cabbage and turnips, all three being
members of the Brassica family. The dual character of the vegetable
is reflected even further in the fact that crunchy, sweet, tangy
kohlrabi is the same vegetable as the woody, stringy, bitter
variety that so often turns people off kohlrabi. The difference
lies in the freshness of the bulb. (Tony Cenicola/New York Times
Photo)
