<HEADLINE>
HITCHCOCK LOOKS FOR SYNTHESIS IN THE STARS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JENNIFER FLOYD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ Stars coach Ken Hitchcock has exchanged his
training-camp grade book for a hockey's version of the periodic
table.
</P>
<P>
   He has begun studying his players' chemistry instead of just his
players.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've had good individual evaluations,'' Hitchcock said
yesterday. ``Now, we'll evaluate line combos together.''
</P>
<P>
   He's looking to see who plays well together, trying to find
chemistry like right winger Jamie Langenbrunner and center Joe
Nieuwendyk had last season.
</P>
<P>
   The Stars' upcoming road swing to Detroit, St. Louis and Chicago
will be his laboratory.
</P>
<P>
   ``When I pull a player out, I will pull the line out,''
Hitchcock said. ``The first five lines we'll pretty much keep as a
group.''
</P>
<P>
   He said he plans to play 12 to 15 of his regulars each game
while trying to trim his roster from almost 50 to about 30 by
Monday.
</P>
<P>
   ``We'll come back on Sunday with a pretty knowledge of our
group,'' Hitchcock said. Planted in the spotlight Center Derek
Plante stood out about as much as George Costanza would at a ``Hair
Club For Men'' meeting when he came to the Stars in a trade last
spring.
</P>
<P>
   Both on and off the ice.
</P>
<P>
   He hasn't had any trouble attracting attention so far in
training camp.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've just liked Plante. He's been a good player for us,''
Hitchcock said. ``It's the new environment thing. It's a lot easier
to bring a role player in. A lot more chemistry goes into being a
skilled player.'' Ringing in the new season Stars goalie Ed Belfour
sat patiently by his locker yesterday as a visitor slipped aluminum
bands around his finger. Yes, it was ring-fitting time around
StarCenter but Belfour wasn't being choosy.
</P>
<P>
   ``Whatever I get I'll be happy with,'' Belfour said. Briefly The
Stars sent goalie Lavente Szuper back to Ottawa of the Ontario
League yesterday. The Stars plan to scrimmage today and tomorrow at
the StarCenter.
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
